    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
        <figcaption><em>Pixel 4, Astrophotography mode; Taken near the San Francisco Ferry Building (i.e. with lots of light pollution). Click for full, uncompressed image.</em></figcaption>
      
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

<p id="b0HuSX">Google is also using that second telephoto lens to improve its portrait mode. It’s better than it was on the Pixel 3, but I don’t think it has caught up to the iPhone 11 Pro. The iPhone has a more elegant drop-off on the background blur and also tends to manage hair better. Both, of course, still look like phone versions of bokeh, not a big DLSR lens. </p>
<div id="AG0Qu7">
